1. how to run shell script?

open terminal under setup folder, run command "sudo chmod a+x setup.sh", then "./setup.sh".

2. what if setup.sh can not install the docker properly?

Please manually install the docker on ubuntu first, here is the installation instruction: https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-and-use-docker-on-ubuntu-18-04
* please take note, the setup.sh is for ubuntu version 18.04. 
